properties.headline: High Wind Watch issued January 7 at 1:34PM MST until January 9 at 5:00AM MST by NWS Cheyenne WY
properties.description:
...HIGH WIND WARNING HAS BEEN EXTENDED FOR PORTIONS OF INTERSTATE
25 AND INTERSTATE 80 THROUGH THIS AFTERNOON...

The National Weather Service in Cheyenne has issued a High Wind
Watch, which is in effect from Wednesday morning through late
Wednesday night.

* WHAT...West winds 35 to 50 mph with gusts of 60 to 70 mph
possible.

* WHERE...Southeast Wyoming including the central and southern
Laramie Range. Included areas along and just east of the
Interstate 25 corridor from the Colorado border to Glendo.

* WHEN...High Wind Warning will expire at 11 am this morning.
High Wind Watch remains in effect Wednesday through Thursday
morning.

* IMPACTS...Mainly to transportation. Strong cross winds can
cause blow overs especially for light and high profile
vehicles. Blowing snow will be an issue near the mountains,
reducing visibilities around one half mile with gusts to 75
MPH possible.
properties.instruction:
A High Wind Watch means there is the potential for a hazardous
high wind event. Sustained winds of at least 40 mph...or gusts of
58 mph or stronger may occur. Continue to monitor the latest
forecasts.

NWSheadline: HIGH WIND WATCH REMAINS IN EFFECT FROM WEDNESDAY MORNING THROUGH LATE WEDNESDAY NIGHT
